name: exploring gender identity
definition: A gender identity in question or in the process of being questioned.

name: no gender identity
definition: An indication that no gender identity has developed. Use for neonates whose assigned sex at birth is 'undifferentiated'. For a person who identifies as not having a gender, use 'non-gendered identity'.

name: nonbinary gender identity
definition: Having an identity considered nonbinary or as falling under the nonbinary umbrella.

name: exclusive gender identity
definition: A gender which has a certain prerequisite which may be unrelated to gender, such as one belonging to a particular culture or indigenous group.

name: fluctuating gender identity
definition: Having a gender identity which fluctuates or switches (such as being male sometimes and female other times).

name: indescribable gender identity
definition: Any of various gender identities defined by their inability to be described, communicated, or otherwise understood.

name: multiple gender identity
definition: Having a multiple gender identities simultaneously.

name: non-gendered identity
definition: Having a gender identity that is genderless or having no gender identity whatsoever.

name: overlapping gender identity
definition: Having a gender identity which overlaps somewhat with other gender identities but not in their entirety.

name: partial gender identity
definition: Having a gender identity which includes part of another gender identity, but not all of it (for example, identifying somewhat with female, but not entirely).

name: other gender identity
definition: A datum representing a person's gender identity which is not listed.

name: unknown gender identity
definition: A datum representing that a person's gender identity is not known for any of various reasons.

name: undisclosed gender identity
definition: A datum representing when an individual does not wish to disclose their gender identity, thereby making their gender identity unknown.
